AC   O22436;
Magnesium-chelatase subunit chlI, chloroplast precursor (EC 6.6.1.1)
(Mg-protoporphyrin IX chelatase).
"Isolation and characterisation of tobacco (Nicotiana tabacum) cDNA
clones encoding proteins involved in magnesium chelation into
protoporphyrin IX.";
-!- FUNCTION: Involved in chlorophyll biosynthesis; introduces a
    magnesium ion into protoporphyrin IX to yield Mg-protoporphyrin
    IX.
-!- CATALYTIC ACTIVITY: ATP + protoporphyrin IX + Mg(2+) + H(2)O = ADP
    + phosphate + Mg-protoporphyrin IX + 2 H(+).
-!- PATHWAY: Chlorophyll biosynthesis.
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Plastid; chloroplast; chloroplast stroma.
-!- TISSUE SPECIFICITY: Strongly expressed in young leaves and to a
    lesser extent in mature leaves.
-!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the Mg-chelatase subunits D/I family.
ATP-binding; Chlorophyll biosynthesis; Chloroplast; Ligase;
Nucleotide-binding; Photosynthesis; Plastid; Transit peptide.
TMZERO
